column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-30 19:24:56" "Youth opposition leader killed in Venezuela vote" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59836180.cms"" />A youth opposition leader was killed in Venezuela on Sunday in a protest against a contentious election organized by President Nicolas Maduro, prosecutors said."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-30 16:32:06" "US successfully tests missile intercept system" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59834200.cms"" />American forces successfully tried out on Sunday a missile interception system the US hopes to set up on the Korean peninsula, military officials said following a trial just days after North Korea's second test of an ICBM."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-30 16:09:03" "Two dead, four wounded in German nightclub shooting" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59834043.cms"" />A gunman opened fire at a packed nightclub in southern Germany on Sunday, killing one and wounding four before being shot by police, authorities said, in an attack likely motivated by a personal feud."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-30 13:07:22" "UK TV to air Princess Diana's recordings on failed marriage" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59832509.cms"" />A British television channel is broadcasting a new documentary on Princess Diana using video tapes in which she candidly discussed her marital problems and her strained relationship with the royal family."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-30 11:18:04" "'Arab states hoped to impose more sanctions on Qatar'" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59831633.cms"" />Saudi Arabia, Egypt, the United Arab Emirates (UAE) and Bahrain are expected to discuss imposing new economic sanctions on Qatar when they meet in the Bahraini capital Manama on Sunday, the pan-Arab al-Hayat newspaper reported."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-30 16:05:54" "Saudi Arabia says calls for internationalization of holy sites 'a declaration of war'" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59834018.cms"" />Saudi Arabia's foreign minister called Qatar's demands for an internationalization of the Muslim hajj pilgrimage a declaration of war against the kingdom, Saudi-owned Al Arabiya television said on Sunday, although it was unclear whether Qatar had actually made any such demand."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-30 08:49:21" "Very disappointed with China on N Korea: Trump" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59830543.cms"" />""I am very disappointed in China. Our foolish past leaders have allowed them to make hundreds of billions of dollars a year in trade, yet they do NOTHING for us with North Korea, just talk,"" Trump said in two tweets yesterday."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-30 08:52:50" "Pakistan to elect new PM on Tuesday" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59830594.cms"" />The Supreme Court on Friday disqualified 67-year-old Sharif for dishonesty and ruled that corruption cases be filed against him and his children over the Panama Papers scandal, forcing the embattled leader out of office."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-30 05:44:48" "Typhoon injures 81 in Taiwan" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59829090.cms"" />Taiwan's first typhoon of the year left 81 people injured and coastal towns flooded as the island braced for a second tropical storm on Sunday. Howling winds toppled motor scooters and hit people with flying glass, the Central Emergency Operations Center said. I"

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-30 04:55:48" "Xi inspects troops on military's 90th anniversary" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59828800.cms"" />It was the first time China has marked Army Day, which formally falls on Aug. 1, with a military parade since the Communist revolution in 1949, state news agency Xinhua said. It was also the first time Xi has reviewed troops in the field like this, Xinhua added."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-29 18:13:46" "Hamburg stabbing suspect known as radical" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59824836.cms"" />A Palestinian man who allegedly stabbed one person to death and wounded six others in Hamburg was known to authorities as a suspected Islamic radical but is also psychologically unstable, German officials said on Saturday."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-29 13:10:18" "Iran says US Navy fired warning shots near its vessels" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59822201.cms"" />Iran's elite Revolutionary Guard said on Saturday a US Navy aircraft carrier fired a warning shot in an ""unprofessional"" confrontation with Iranian vessels, the official IRNA news agency reported."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-29 14:17:14" "Nawaz Sharif's disqualification will not affect CPEC: China" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59823009.cms"" />China has said that Nawaz Sharif's disqualification from Pakistan's premiership will not affect its $50 billion China-Pakistan Economic Corridor project, amid reports that some of Beijing's big ticket investments in the country may come under a widening corruption probe."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-29 18:55:00" "Trump fires chief of staff as White House chaos continues" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59825258.cms"" />US President Donald Trump on Friday sacked his chief of staff Reince Priebus and replaced him with Homeland Security Secretary John Kelly in what is now ceaseless White House drama widely seen as bordering on the farcical."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-29 12:09:09" "For Trump, the honeymoon with Putin may be finally over" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59821736.cms"" />Russia's tit-for-tat decision to expel hundreds of US diplomats and seize two US compounds may be an acknowledgment in Moscow that Trump's ability to bring better ties is limited, at best, and the start of a new downward spiral in relations."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-29 12:02:54" "Struggling to govern, Trump faces Republican unease" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59821677.cms"" />As fellow Republicans labored to repeal Obamacare this week, US President Donald Trump repeatedly swerved off-topic, escalating concerns in his party about his ability to govern the country six months after taking office."

column1: en_IND_tindia_int "2017-07-29 08:31:47" "Sri Lanka, China sign long delayed $1.5 bn port deal" "
column3: src=""http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/59819660.cms"" />Sri Lanka's government has signed a long-delayed agreement to sell a 70-percent stake in the $1.5 billion Hambantota port to China in a bid to recover from the heavy burden of repayment of loans obtained to build the port."
